# tinyproxy.conf.tmpl — domain-allowlist forward proxy for the microVM egress
# (Analysis S-C). TEMPLATE: fill ${ALLOWLIST} (an absolute path to worker-allow.txt
# or broker-allow.txt) and render/copy to tinyproxy.conf.
#
# This is the tier the nft files cannot provide: nft is a PORT + LAN allowlist,
# but "only github/pypi/openai/telegram/…" is a per-DOMAIN policy. tinyproxy
# applies the domain allowlist to both plain HTTP requests and HTTPS CONNECT
# targets, default-deny — so egress is restricted to named hosts, not "any 443".

Port 8888
# With QEMU SLIRP the guest reaches the host loopback as 10.0.2.2, so a proxy bound
# to 127.0.0.1 here is reachable from the Worker as http://10.0.2.2:8888. On the
# Broker side, bind 127.0.0.1 and point the Broker's https_proxy at it locally.
Listen 127.0.0.1
Timeout 600

# Only the local host (the SLIRP NAT / the Broker process) may use the proxy.
Allow 127.0.0.1

# Domain allowlist: default-deny, only hosts matching a line in ${ALLOWLIST} pass.
Filter "${ALLOWLIST}"
FilterDefaultDeny Yes
FilterExtended On
FilterCaseSensitive Off

# HTTPS is CONNECT to 443; allow 80 for plain metadata/mirror endpoints.
ConnectPort 443
ConnectPort 80

# No disk cache of proxied content; quiet logging.
LogLevel Warning
